What does Attribution mean?

It means you must attribute the authors. Use my name in all attribution
instances, and preferably also my HAM identifier where you think this is
appropriate.

Examples:
"We thank Christian Križan for sharing instrument control code."
"Based on code developed by Christian Križan SA6KRZ and code contributors."

Omitting the surname caron above z is appropriate where there are technical
limitations that prohibit an extended character.



What does Non Commercial mean?

Non Commercial means that you are not allowed to make money on this code,
and because of the SA clause, no-one may make money based on derivatives
of this code. If you want to use derivatives of this work commercially,
I am open to discussions on commercial licensing and royalty, contact me on
christian.krizan@gmail.com or look up my details via my registered identifier
SA6KRZ.



What does Share Alike mean?

It means that you as an adapter subject to follow Creative Commons' rules
for applying this license to your derivative work. You cannot copy-paste
the files, change the name of some variables, and suddenly get full and
unquestionably exclusive ownership to the copyright as a cheap excuse to
avoid my terms. See the Creative Commons license link for further details.
De facto this means that if you copy the code and make changes, you must
still acknowledge that you are using code originally made by the original
author. And, you may typically not make money on your copy.


Disputes and details as to licensed use of this contract is to be handled
in a court of law, selected by the original author.
